# 5. Important Test Cases (Examples)

## Test Case 1: Login Validation
- Verify users can log in with valid credentials
- Verify invalid credentials show error message

## Test Case 2: Patient Record Creation
- Verify patient details are saved correctly
- Verify mandatory fields cannot be left empty

## Test Case 3: Appointment Scheduling
- Verify appointments are created successfully
- Verify duplicate appointments are prevented

## Test Case 4: Billing Validation
- Verify bill amount calculations are correct
- Verify payment records are stored properly

## Test Case 5: Report Generation
- Verify reports display accurate data
- Verify reports load successfully

---

# 6. Reflection: Why Enterprise Software Development Needs Structured Workflows

Enterprise software systems are large and complex. Structured workflows are necessary to ensure proper development, testing, deployment, and maintenance.

Reasons:
- Improves organization
- Reduces development errors
- Enhances teamwork and collaboration
- Ensures software quality
- Makes maintenance easier
- Supports scalability
- Protects business data

Structured workflows help organizations develop reliable, secure, and efficient enterprise applications.
